            <abstract encodinganalog="520$a">Files documenting Philip Wagner's career as a freelance columnist, writer and editor for the Baltimore Sun and Baltimore Evening Sun, and founder of Boordy Vineyard. Includes correspondence, manuscripts, clippings, research files, case files, publications, diaries, notes and photos. Significant correspondents represented are: Alfred Knopf, H.L. Mencken, Knowles Ryerson, Knud Meister, Ann Duchene, Lord Winster.</abstract>
